  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HARNESSING THE POTENTIAL OF OIL TO CONTRIBUTE TO UGANDA&#x2019;S PEACEFUL DEVELOPMENT &#x2013; PHASE 3.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective one: To strengthen inter-ministerial coordination and stakeholder participation in the dissemination and implementation of the National Action Plan on Gender and Extractives (NAPGE) at both national and community levels.

Objective two: To support processes and actions aimed at prevention, mitigation and peaceful resolution of oil sector conflicts through research and analysis, joint advocacy, skills training and problem-solving meetings.

Objective three: To promote the implementation of conflict sensitive business practices, voluntary principles (VPs) on security and human rights and constructive company-community engagement working collaboratively with IOC&#x2019;s and their contractors, security agencies and DGF supported CSO&#x2019;s.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This 19 month project aims to contribute to Uganda&#x2019;s peaceful development by harnessing opportunities in the oil sector, as it moves from exploration to the early production phase. It brings together government, oil companies and communities living in areas of high oil reserves to develop joint strategies. Consolidating the successes of an earlier phase of the project, it will scale up conflict sensitive business practice within the oil sector, strengthen conflict resolution and prevention mechanisms at the district and national levels and directly support the Government of Uganda in implementing the National Action Plan on Gender and Extractives.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Uganda government, oil companies and communities living in areas of high oil reserves</narrative>
